The paper discusses the use of algorithms and technology to regulate society, which falls under the category of computational social science (cs.CY) and social computing (cs.SOC). The paper also discusses the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and cybersecurity (cs.CR) in implementing algorithmic regulation. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of reputation management systems and mechanism design, which are topics related to social informatics (cs.SI).
